<node id="GraphRAG">
  <data key="d0">GraphRAG</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">GraphRAG is a RAG system that uses a community-based traversal method, which LightRAG aims to reduce retrieval overhead compared to.&lt;SEP&gt;A graph-enhanced RAG system that uses an LLM to extract entities and relationships, represents them as nodes and edges, and produces community reports for global information.&lt;SEP&gt;GraphRAG is a graph-based RAG system that uses retrieval mechanisms, which is consistently outperformed by LightRAG, especially in larger datasets with complex language contexts.&lt;SEP&gt;A competitive baseline method that LightRAG is compared against in case studies.&lt;SEP&gt;GraphRAG is a model that exhibits significant inefficiency in managing newly added data, requiring the dismantling and regeneration of its community structure, incurring substantial token costs.&lt;SEP&gt;A baseline method compared with LightRAG, characterized by generating communities and higher token and API call consumption during retrieval.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fef3e239f1910dc4633864fe3bf43b2f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c67b3382f509ac5b049a984b30f29c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-406bf69e556a29330cb91c63e689dffc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45c46ee88a9a2d60d923862ae51dbb45</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751022</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="NaiveRAG">
  <data key="d0">NaiveRAG</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">NaiveRAG is a purely chunk-based retrieval method that serves as a baseline, consistently outperformed by graph-enhanced RAG systems, and is used as a reference in ablation studies.&lt;SEP&gt;A foundational framework or system from which different retrieval variants are explored.&lt;SEP&gt;NaiveRAG is a baseline information retrieval model that provides informative responses but lacks the depth needed to thoroughly examine certain dimensions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45c46ee88a9a2d60d923862ae51dbb45&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dd4ed1717f8c1090154df49ba8cb327a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751022</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="HyDE">
  <data key="d0">HyDE</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A method that employs an LLM to generate a hypothetical document based on an input query, which is then used for retrieving relevant text chunks.&lt;SEP&gt;HyDE is a purely chunk-based retrieval method that is consistently outperformed by graph-enhanced RAG systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fef3e239f1910dc4633864fe3bf43b2f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751022</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="RQRAG">
  <data key="d0">RQRAG</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">RQRAG is a purely chunk-based retrieval method that is consistently outperformed by graph-enhanced RAG systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751022</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Graph-Enhanced RAG Systems">
  <data key="d0">Graph-Enhanced RAG Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Graph-Enhanced RAG Systems are a category of Retrieval Augmented Generation systems that leverage graph-based structures, consistently outperforming purely chunk-based methods in large-scale corpora and complex queries.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751022</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Purely Chunk-Based Retrieval Methods">
  <data key="d0">Purely Chunk-Based Retrieval Methods</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Purely Chunk-Based Retrieval Methods are a category of retrieval methods that rely on text chunks, generally outperformed by graph-enhanced RAG systems, particularly as dataset size increases.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751022</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Large-Scale Corpora">
  <data key="d0">Large-Scale Corpora</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Large-Scale Corpora are datasets characterized by large token counts and complex queries, serving as a primary context for evaluating RAG system performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751022</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Complex Queries">
  <data key="d0">Complex Queries</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Queries that span multiple document chunks, which LightRAG's graph structures are enhanced to handle.&lt;SEP&gt;Complex Queries require a thorough understanding of the dataset's context and are handled effectively by graph-enhanced RAG systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Queries that demand comprehensive insights, with which NaiveRAG -High struggles to gather information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47f20c669a70fff5620e01924436985d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45c46ee88a9a2d60d923862ae51dbb45</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751023</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Legal Dataset">
  <data key="d0">Legal Dataset</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The Legal Dataset is one of the four domains from the UltraDomain benchmark, centering on corporate legal practices.&lt;SEP&gt;One of the four datasets used for evaluating RAG systems.&lt;SEP&gt;The Legal Dataset is the largest dataset mentioned, where graph-enhanced RAG systems, especially LightRAG, show dominant performance and win rates.&lt;SEP&gt;The legal dataset is a specific dataset used as a reference point for the size of newly introduced data.&lt;SEP&gt;The specific dataset used for evaluating the model cost and adaptability of LightRAG and GraphRAG.&lt;SEP&gt;The largest dataset, comprising 94 documents and 5,081,069 tokens, detailed in Table 4.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fef3e239f1910dc4633864fe3bf43b2f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c67b3382f509ac5b049a984b30f29c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-406bf69e556a29330cb91c63e689dffc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c80e23a4f1cc3df3c051d5673ddddb5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751023</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Response Diversity">
  <data key="d0">Response Diversity</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Response Diversity refers to the ability of a system to generate a wider range of varied responses, a significant advantage of LightRAG.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751023</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Diversity Metric">
  <data key="d0">Diversity Metric</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Diversity Metric is a specific evaluation criterion used to measure the variety of responses generated by a system, where LightRAG shows a consistent lead.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751023</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dual-Level Retrieval Paradigm">
  <data key="d0">Dual-Level Retrieval Paradigm</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Dual-Level Retrieval Paradigm is a mechanism in LightRAG that facilitates efficient retrieval of related entities and relations and enhances comprehensiveness.&lt;SEP&gt;The dual-level retrieval paradigm is an approach integrated into LightRAG, designed to capture both low-level and high-level information for comprehensive and cost-effective retrieval.&lt;SEP&gt;A paradigm proposed by LightRAG for retrieving relevant information by generating query keys at both detailed and abstract levels.&lt;SEP&gt;The Dual-Level Retrieval Paradigm is a core component of LightRAG, facilitating comprehensive information retrieval from both low-level and high-level dimensions, enhancing response diversity.&lt;SEP&gt;The dual-level retrieval paradigm is a method proposed by LightRAG that facilitates rapid retrieval of relevant information and allows for the extraction of specific and abstract information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69aa0eae6d1f6ab69e22f063ae2a2e46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47f20c669a70fff5620e01924436985d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-406bf69e556a29330cb91c63e689dffc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751023</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Graph-Based Text Indexing">
  <data key="d0">Graph-Based Text Indexing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Graph-Based Text Indexing is a technique leveraged by LightRAG's dual-level retrieval paradigm to effectively capture the full context in response to queries.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751023</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Low-Level Retrieval">
  <data key="d0">Low-Level Retrieval</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A retrieval strategy focused on retrieving specific entities along with their associated attributes or relationships, addressing detail-oriented queries.&lt;SEP&gt;Low-Level Retrieval is a component of LightRAG's dual-level retrieval paradigm, focused on retrieving specific entities.&lt;SEP&gt;A component of LightRAG's hierarchical retrieval paradigm focused on in-depth explorations of related entities to enhance empowerment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c67b3382f509ac5b049a984b30f29c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47f20c669a70fff5620e01924436985d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751023</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High-Level Retrieval">
  <data key="d0">High-Level Retrieval</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A retrieval strategy that addresses broader topics and overarching themes, aggregating information across multiple related entities and relationships for higher-level concepts and summaries.&lt;SEP&gt;High-Level Retrieval is a component of LightRAG's dual-level retrieval paradigm, focused on retrieving broader topics.&lt;SEP&gt;A component of LightRAG's hierarchical retrieval paradigm focused on broader explorations to improve answer diversity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c67b3382f509ac5b049a984b30f29c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47f20c669a70fff5620e01924436985d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751023</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Agriculture Dataset">
  <data key="d0">Agriculture Dataset</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The Agriculture Dataset is one of the four domains from the UltraDomain benchmark, focusing on agricultural practices.&lt;SEP&gt;One of the four datasets used for evaluating RAG systems.&lt;SEP&gt;The Agriculture Dataset is one of the datasets, containing millions of tokens, used to demonstrate LightRAG's superiority over GraphRAG.&lt;SEP&gt;A specific dataset where the -Origin variant showed improvements.&lt;SEP&gt;A dataset consisting of 12 documents and 2,017,886 tokens, detailed in Table 4.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fef3e239f1910dc4633864fe3bf43b2f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-406bf69e556a29330cb91c63e689dffc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45c46ee88a9a2d60d923862ae51dbb45&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c80e23a4f1cc3df3c051d5673ddddb5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751023</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CS Dataset">
  <data key="d0">CS Dataset</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The CS Dataset is one of the four domains from the UltraDomain benchmark, focusing on computer science, data science, and software engineering.&lt;SEP&gt;One of the four datasets used for evaluating RAG systems.&lt;SEP&gt;The CS Dataset is one of the datasets, containing millions of tokens, used to demonstrate LightRAG's superiority over GraphRAG.&lt;SEP&gt;A dataset containing 10 documents and 2,306,535 tokens, detailed in Table 4.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fef3e239f1910dc4633864fe3bf43b2f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-406bf69e556a29330cb91c63e689dffc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c80e23a4f1cc3df3c051d5673ddddb5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751023</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ablation Studies (RQ2)">
  <data key="d0">Ablation Studies (RQ2)</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Ablation Studies (RQ2) are research conducted to evaluate the individual impact and effectiveness of LightRAG's dual-level retrieval paradigm and graph-based text indexing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751023</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Table 2">
  <data key="d0">Table 2</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Table 2 is a presentation of results from ablation studies, detailing the performance of ablated versions of LightRAG with NaiveRAG as a reference.&lt;SEP&gt;A table presenting the results of the model cost and adaptability analysis on the legal dataset.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c67b3382f509ac5b049a984b30f29c0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751023</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Comprehensiveness (Metric)">
  <data key="d0">Comprehensiveness (Metric)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Comprehensiveness is a performance metric used in evaluating RAG systems, indicating the thoroughness of information understanding.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751023</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Empowerment (Metric)">
  <data key="d0">Empowerment (Metric)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Empowerment is a performance metric used in evaluating RAG systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dc9482cd15753defdf374f6e33adf94</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751023</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Overall (Metric)">
