<node id="LLM">
  <data key="d0">LLM</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Large Language Model that is prompted by the R(·) function to identify entities and relationships, and employed by the P(·) function for key-value pair generation.&lt;SEP&gt;A large language model used for various operations in RAG systems, including query decomposition, hypothetical document generation, entity extraction, evaluation, ranking baselines, and comparing answers.&lt;SEP&gt;A Large Language Model that extracts keywords from a query, is fed structured data, and generates comprehensive answers.&lt;SEP&gt;An expert system, such as a Large Language Model, tasked with evaluating answers based on given criteria.</data>
