<node id="Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)">
  <data key="d0">Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) is a framework that integrates user queries with a collection of pertinent documents sourced from an external knowledge database, incorporating a Retrieval Component and a Generation Component.&lt;SEP&gt;A general method enhanced by semantic graphs, which involves retrieving information to augment generation processes.&lt;SEP&gt;Retrieval-Augmented Generation systems enhance Large Language Model inputs by retrieving relevant information from external sources, grounding responses in factual knowledge.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-69aa0eae6d1f6ab69e22f063ae2a2e46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45c46ee88a9a2d60d923862ae51dbb45</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751029</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Graph Structures">
  <data key="d0">Graph Structures</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A method used in LightRAG for representing interdependencies among entities, integrated into text indexing and retrieval processes.&lt;SEP&gt;Graph structures represent complex interdependencies among entities and are integrated into text indexing within LightRAG.&lt;SEP&gt;Graph structures are integrated into LightRAG's retrieval mechanism and are explored for knowledge representation in recent studies.&lt;SEP&gt;A data organization method integrated into LightRAG's retrieval mechanism.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-69aa0eae6d1f6ab69e22f063ae2a2e46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c67b3382f509ac5b049a984b30f29c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0747de8554c174a10ea77615f403b7d8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751029</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vector Representations">
  <data key="d0">Vector Representations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Integrated with graph structures in LightRAG to facilitate efficient retrieval of related entities and their relationships.&lt;SEP&gt;Vector representations are used with graph structures in the framework to facilitate efficient retrieval of related entities and relations.&lt;SEP&gt;Representations combined with graph structures in LightRAG to gain deeper insight into entity interrelationships and utilize keywords effectively.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-69aa0eae6d1f6ab69e22f063ae2a2e46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47f20c669a70fff5620e01924436985d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0747de8554c174a10ea77615f403b7d8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751029</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Knowledge Graph">
  <data key="d0">Knowledge Graph</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The Knowledge Graph is a structured data representation from which LightRAG integrates relevant structural information.&lt;SEP&gt;A structured representation of information that LightRAG utilizes to enhance the comprehensiveness of retrieval results.&lt;SEP&gt;A knowledge graph is a comprehensive data structure constructed by LightRAG using extracted entities and relationships, highlighting connections and insights across documents.&lt;SEP&gt;A knowledge graph is a structured representation of information that LightRAG utilizes and that recent studies have explored for knowledge representation.&lt;SEP&gt;A structured representation of information used in the dual-level retrieval process to find relevant entities and relationships.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-69aa0eae6d1f6ab69e22f063ae2a2e46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-406bf69e556a29330cb91c63e689dffc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0747de8554c174a10ea77615f403b7d8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c80e23a4f1cc3df3c051d5673ddddb5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751029</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Text Indexing">
  <data key="d0">Text Indexing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A process where LightRAG incorporates graph structures to organize textual information for retrieval.&lt;SEP&gt;Text indexing is the process of integrating graph structures to effectively represent complex interdependencies among entities for RAG systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-69aa0eae6d1f6ab69e22f063ae2a2e46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0747de8554c174a10ea77615f403b7d8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751029</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Incremental Update Algorithm">
  <data key="d0">Incremental Update Algorithm</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A component of LightRAG that ensures timely integration of new data for sustained effectiveness in dynamic environments.&lt;SEP&gt;An incremental update algorithm is a component of LightRAG that ensures timely integration of new data and accelerates adaptation in dynamic environments.&lt;SEP&gt;An algorithm used by LightRAG to process new documents D′ using graph-based indexing steps φ, resulting in new graph data that is combined with existing data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-69aa0eae6d1f6ab69e22f063ae2a2e46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47f20c669a70fff5620e01924436985d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0747de8554c174a10ea77615f403b7d8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751029</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="External Database">
  <data key="d0">External Database</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">An external database is a collection of pertinent documents and information from which Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) systems source data.&lt;SEP&gt;A database external to LightRAG, which serves as a source for the knowledge base and is subject to incremental updates.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-69aa0eae6d1f6ab69e22f063ae2a2e46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47f20c669a70fff5620e01924436985d</data>
